01:14:58.540 --> 01:15:00.710
And so the typical
autocorrelation time

01:15:00.710 --> 01:15:04.480
should be kind of the
cell generation time.

01:15:04.480 --> 01:15:09.820
So what we call the typical time
should be rather generational.

01:15:13.450 --> 01:15:15.080
So indeed, this is
the same as humans.

01:15:15.080 --> 01:15:16.510
We have a well-defined
personality

01:15:16.510 --> 01:15:19.040
and then we pass on some of
our personality to our kids.

01:15:19.040 --> 01:15:21.530
The typical time
scale is a generation.

01:15:21.530 --> 01:15:24.150
So I'm teaching you guys super
useful things in this class.

01:15:24.150 --> 01:15:26.830
I don't want anybody
saying anything else.

01:15:30.780 --> 01:15:34.230
But I think that this
is a neat example of how

01:15:34.230 --> 01:15:36.240
different cells can have
what you might describe

01:15:36.240 --> 01:15:37.948
as being somehow
different personalities,

01:15:37.948 --> 01:15:40.250
but it arises for a
very particular reason

01:15:40.250 --> 01:15:42.960
because this information
is being transmitted

01:15:42.960 --> 01:15:45.112
through this network.

01:15:45.112 --> 01:15:46.570
Now, despite the
fact that they all

01:15:46.570 --> 01:15:48.479
have different chi
R concentrations--

01:15:48.479 --> 01:15:50.520
so they might have different
tumbling frequencies

01:15:50.520 --> 01:15:51.650
and so forth, but
they should all

01:15:51.650 --> 01:15:53.290
be able to display
this phenomenon

01:15:53.290 --> 01:15:56.260
of perfect adaptation.

01:15:56.260 --> 01:15:59.000
So what we then see is
that from the experiments

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:01.170
and from some simple
models, you can

01:16:01.170 --> 01:16:04.300
get insight into how it
is that this phenomenon

01:16:04.300 --> 01:16:06.589
of perfect adaptation
might be robust to changes

01:16:06.589 --> 01:16:08.880
in the concentrations of
different things, particularly

01:16:08.880 --> 01:16:10.820
chi R in this case.

01:16:10.820 --> 01:16:12.960
And chi R is the
dominant source of error

01:16:12.960 --> 01:16:14.760
because it's present
in such small numbers.

